The paper discusses the challenges of designing and developing tangible interfaces for mental well-being, which involves the use of sensors, microcontrollers, and machine learning. This topic falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), which is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper also discusses ethical and privacy concerns, which could fall under the sub-category of Computers and Society (cs.CY). The use of machine learning and sensors also suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the use of microcontrollers could suggest that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of Robotics (cs.RO).
